# Glowmint

Linux-native desktop app for Corsair hardware — an iCUE alternative for Mint and other distros.

**Stack:** Tauri 2 (Rust backend) + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Vite.

## App areas

| Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `/` (Dashboard) | Device overview, backend health, setup banner |
| `/aio` | Elite AIO LCD + pump/fan cooling |
| `/lighting` | RGB zones and lighting modes |
| `/peripherals` | Keyboards, mice — RGB, DPI, profiles |
| `/setup` | System checks, udev rules, backend setup |
| Welcome wizard | First-run onboarding (blocks main app until complete/skipped) |

## Hardware backends

| Area | Backend | Driver path |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Elite AIO LCD | Native Rust HID | `src-tauri/src/drivers/corsair_lcd/` |
| Pump / fans | liquidctl | `src-tauri/src/drivers/liquidctl.rs` |
| RGB lighting | OpenRGB | `src-tauri/src/drivers/openrgb.rs` |
| Keyboards / mice | ckb-next | `src-tauri/src/drivers/ckb_next.rs` |

Profiles (save/load LCD, cooling, RGB settings) are persisted via `profile_service` + `profile_store`.

## Architecture

Layered flow: **React UI → `src/lib/api.ts` (invoke) → Tauri commands (`state.rs`) → services → drivers → hardware**.

| Layer | Path |
| --- | --- |
| Pages | `src/pages/` |
| Feature UI | `src/features/` |
| API | `src/lib/api.ts`, `src/lib/types.ts` |
| IPC | `src-tauri/src/state.rs` |
| Services | `src-tauri/src/services/` |
| Domain | `src-tauri/src/domain/` (pure types/traits — no Tauri/USB imports) |
| Drivers | `src-tauri/src/drivers/` |

See `CONTRIBUTING.md` for where new code goes and how to add a backend.

## Dev commands

```bash
npm run tauri dev   # run app
cargo test          # Rust tests (from src-tauri/)
npm run lint        # eslint + prettier
```
